The '''Meteosat visible and infrared imager''' (or MVIRI) is the scientific instrument package on board the seven [[Meteosat]] first-generation [[geostationary]] [[Weather satellite|meteorological satellites]].  This [[Measuring instrument|instrument]] is capable of capturing images in the [[Visible spectrum|visible]], [[infrared]], and [[Water vapor#Radar and satellite imaging|water vapor]] regions of the [[electromagnetic spectrum]].

