{{Infobox NRHP | name = Scott and Roberts Dry Cleaning Plant, Office, and Store | nrhp_type = | image = | caption = | location= 733 Foster St., [[Durham, North Carolina]] | coordinates = {{coord|36|00|18|N|78|54|06|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = North Carolina#USA | built = {{Start date|1947}} | architect = | builder = | architecture = Moderne | added = June 20, 2012 | area = {{convert|.397|acre}} | governing_body = Private | mpsub = | refnum = 12000345<ref name="nps">{{cite web|url=http://www.nps.gov/nr/listings/20120629.htm|title=National Register of Historic Places Listings|date=2012-06-29|work=Weekly List of Actions Taken on Properties: 6/18/12 through 6/22/12|publisher=National Park Service}}</ref> }} '''Scott and Roberts Dry Cleaning Plant, Office, and Store''' is a historic [[dry cleaning]] plant, [[office]], and store located at [[Durham, North Carolina|Durham]], [[Durham County, North Carolina]]. It was built in 1947, and is a one-story, three bay [[Streamline Moderne|Moderne]] brick building on a partial [[concrete]] basement. It features a projecting center bay, plate-glass storefront windows, and a centered front entrance with original glass-block entrance surround.<ref name = nrhpinv>{{Cite web | author = Cynthia de Miranda | title=Scott and Roberts Dry Cleaning Plant, Office, and Store| work = National Register of Historic Places - Nomination and Inventory | date = October 2011| url = http://www.hpo.ncdcr.gov/nr/DH2862.pdf | format = pdf | publisher = North Carolina State Historic Preservation Office | accessdate = 2014-10-01}}</ref>
